&lt;p&gt;Review request for hbase.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Summary&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a problem we observed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3008&quot; title=&quot;Memstore.updateColumnValue passes wrong flag to heapSizeChange&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3008&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3008&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; + &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2997&quot; title=&quot;Performance fixes - profiler driven&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2997&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2997&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, that memstore sizes can go negative preventing us from flushing them even if there is data within.  This is a data loss bug.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This addresses bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3008&quot; title=&quot;Memstore.updateColumnValue passes wrong flag to heapSizeChange&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3008&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3008&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
